# <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="30" /> Puzzler

Puzzler is a game that generates a block puzzle form an image.  The currently implemented mode allows the user to generate an puzzle from a random image using the Unsplash random image interface (https://source.unsplash.com/).  The user can optionally specify a subject matter for the image and specifies the number of rows and columns to "puzzlify" the image.

<img src="PuzzlerDemo.png"/>

## Installation

Install Rails using an installation guide like the guide from RailsGuides: https://guides.rubyonrails.org/getting_started.html.

Install a server application.  For the sake of example, lite-server will be used.  Install lite-server per the installation instructions in the `README.md` in the lite-server github project https://github.com/johnpapa/lite-server.

Fork and clone the front end project https://github.com/Douglas-J-Johnson/module3-frontend.
Fork and clone the back end project https://github.com/Douglas-J-Johnson/module3-backend.  Migrate the back end database using `rails db:migrate`.

## Usage
As initially configured, serve up the back end on port 3000 using `rails s` an serve up the front end on port 3001 by running `lite-server` (lite server will grab the next available port starting with 3000 by default).
